						<summary>

						<p>Pillar lying in the street to the south-west of the market site.</p>						

						<p>This undated inscription may be assigned to the 13th century, on the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>It states that the pillar was set up in the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> of the Mahādēvīśvara temple by Bōlōju, son of Nuṅkōju.</p>						

						</summary>
